Reference - 
Watch striver Lazy Propagation - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rwXVCELcrqU
# Approach
Lazy Propagation Segment tree technique
seg[ind] = no. of 1's between low - high

therefore no. of zeros = (high - low + 1) - seg[ind]
i.e: zero = range - (no. of 1's)
so, in lazy, we are are just storing the parity 
if lazy[ind] = 1, reverse the no. of 1's to no. of zero
swap(no. of ones, no. of zeros)

query 2:
nums2[i] += nums1[i]*p
let sum = sum of all elements in nums2
this basically means:
newSum = sum + (no. of 1's)*p[ let say it " s "]
every time query 2 is called
s += (no of 1's)*p
query 3:
sum of num2 element + (sum of no. of time query 2 is done, that is store it in some variable " s ")
# Complexity
- For every rangeUpadate and rangeQuery -> O(logN)


