# Intuition
Split nums1 into sqrt(n) blocks. For each block, count the number of 1s in it. And also whether the whole block is reversed or not.



# Approach
For each type-1 query,
We can update the whole blocks together by setting rev[block_id] = !rev[block_id] and update the total number of 1s in that block.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n ^ 1.5) per type-1 query

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<long long> handleQuery(vector<int>& nums1, vector<int>& nums2, vector<vector<int>>& queries) {
        const int n = nums1.size(), size = sqrt(n + 1.), m = (n + size - 1) / size;
        vector<int> s(m);
        vector<bool> rev(m);
        vector<long long> r;
        long long total = 0, v = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            s[i / size] += nums1[i];
            total += nums1[i];
            v += nums2[i];
        }
        for (const auto & q : queries) {
            if (q[0] == 1) {
